      "writtenOn": "2017-10-16T22:59:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree it\u0027s overkill, but the alternative isn\u0027t great as there\u0027s no reason to pass in a function like that except for testing purposes. I looked around through Milo (which does this exact pattern to mock pubsub editing) and through the various GAE abstractions (logging, datastore) and they all do the same thing. I I think I would like to move this into [gitiles] or something and instead make the interface Log, LogForward, and whatever else it provides.\n\nThe issue with that is it\u0027ll take a bit of work to get that in, test it, and fix up everything that depends on [gitiles]. I pushed this here in order to try out this testing model for the gitiles API, and I think it works well? If it\u0027s OK I\u0027d like to leave this here for now, but if it\u0027s too much then I can move it out now.",
